<subSubSection id="86F8A0C7FF842458FE93FEEF17D3FCCB" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CE5DF34CFF842458FE93FEEF1413FEE8" blockId="27.[264,1323,356,862]" box="[264,383,356,381]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="FC962F5EFF842458FE93FEEF1413FEE8" box="[264,383,356,381]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE5DF34CFF842458FEA3FE071715FD03" blockId="27.[264,1323,356,862]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Dark brown to black, base of elytron with brick red marks. Pronotum transverse with lateral margin strongly convex (
<figureCitation id="56D9EFC9FF842458FD19FE3F178EFE5B" box="[642,738,436,462]" captionStart="FIGURE 7. A. A" captionStartId="14.[264,367,1433,1457]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,477,1408]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[302,1293,466,1408]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 7. A. A. sordidus, pronotum (dorsal view); B. A. guttatus, prosternum (lateral view); C. A. guttatus, prosternum (ventral view); D. A. atratus, left elytron, dashed line indicates explanate margin; E. A. sordidus, left elytron, dashed line indicates explanate margin; F. A. sordidus, anal sclerite (ventral view); G. A. kauaiensis, apex of anal sclerite; H. Orthostolus nsp., metafemur (ventral view); I. A. guttatus, metafemur (ventral view); J. A. guttatus, labial palp (ventral view); K. Eupetinus impressus, labial palp (ventral view); L A. atratus, anal sclerite (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175095/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number id="782AE16BFF842458FD21FE3F17A5FE5B" box="[698,713,436,462]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="7.0">7</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). Elytron with lateral margin narrow, 
<date id="BA5CD58CFF842458FB3AFE3F11D2FE5B" box="[1185,1214,436,462]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<number id="782AE16BFF842458FB3AFE3F11C3FE5B" box="[1185,1199,436,462]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
width of bead at middle, sometimes wider at humeri (
<figureCitation id="56D9EFC9FF842458FC97FE57163DFE63" box="[780,849,476,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 7. A. A" captionStartId="14.[264,367,1433,1457]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,477,1408]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[302,1293,466,1408]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 7. A. A. sordidus, pronotum (dorsal view); B. A. guttatus, prosternum (lateral view); C. A. guttatus, prosternum (ventral view); D. A. atratus, left elytron, dashed line indicates explanate margin; E. A. sordidus, left elytron, dashed line indicates explanate margin; F. A. sordidus, anal sclerite (ventral view); G. A. kauaiensis, apex of anal sclerite; H. Orthostolus nsp., metafemur (ventral view); I. A. guttatus, metafemur (ventral view); J. A. guttatus, labial palp (ventral view); K. Eupetinus impressus, labial palp (ventral view); L A. atratus, anal sclerite (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175095/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number id="782AE16BFF842458FCD9FE57163DFE63" box="[834,849,476,502]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Pale marks on elytra most prominent along base, often continuing along suture to apical margin. Male pygidium narrow, subtruncate to shallowly emarginate, anal sclerite with lateral apical margin concave and convergent, apex acuminate (
<figureCitation id="56D9EFC9FF842458FDF5FDDF17D4FDFB" box="[622,696,596,622]" captionStart="FIGURE 7. A. A" captionStartId="14.[264,367,1433,1457]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,477,1408]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[302,1293,466,1408]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 7. A. A. sordidus, pronotum (dorsal view); B. A. guttatus, prosternum (lateral view); C. A. guttatus, prosternum (ventral view); D. A. atratus, left elytron, dashed line indicates explanate margin; E. A. sordidus, left elytron, dashed line indicates explanate margin; F. A. sordidus, anal sclerite (ventral view); G. A. kauaiensis, apex of anal sclerite; H. Orthostolus nsp., metafemur (ventral view); I. A. guttatus, metafemur (ventral view); J. A. guttatus, labial palp (ventral view); K. Eupetinus impressus, labial palp (ventral view); L A. atratus, anal sclerite (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175095/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number id="782AE16BFF842458FD32FDDF17D4FDFB" box="[681,696,596,622]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
F), broader at base than apex of pygidium. Length 
<quantity id="091A5EA9FF842458FE93FDF714FDFD03" box="[264,401,636,662]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="5.05" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.6">4.6–5.5mm</quantity>
, Width 
<quantity id="091A5EA9FF842458FE77FDF71719FD03" box="[492,629,636,662]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="2.0999999999999996" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.3mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
